<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-06-14T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-06-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="519" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d519">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.51632 National City Bank/35:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Morgan</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-06-14T13:00:00-04:00">June 14, 1930—1
                                p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>42. Your 33, June 11, 3 p.m., last paragraph. The Secretary spoke with
                            Senhor Freitas Valle this morning regarding the matter emphasizing the
                            desirability of a rapid settlement. Mr. Valle promised to cable to Rio
                            regarding it.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>